if you agree with the statement, you can use an asterisk (*) after the sentence to indicate that you completely agree with the statement. For example:

- All religions are socially constructed and none are objectively true.

if you disagree with the statement, you can use an asterisk (*) before the sentence to indicate that you do not agree with the statement. For example:

- All religions are socially constructed and all religions are false.

if you refuse to answer, you can use an asterisk (*) in the empty space after the statement. For example:

- I do not have a preference for any religion.

note that you can use asterisks in any sentence or statement, not just those related to religions.
